OL,6,FHe said Ireland had lost "a giant of
OL,7,Fpublic service broadcasting".
OL,9,FDirector-general of RTE Kevin Bakhurst
OL,10,Fsaid Mr Davin-Power had "one of the
OL,11,Fmost incisive political brains at RTE
OL,12,Fand indeed in Ireland".
OL,14,F"For many years, he was familiar to
OL,15,Faudiences, colleagues and politicians
OL,16,Fas insightful, eloquent and
OL,17,Fscrupulously fair. Off-screen, he was
OL,18,Falso funny, a great storyteller and
OL,19,Fwas hugely loyal to colleagues,
OL,20,Ffriends and to RTE itself.
OL,26,@nD@ZOUoD@\O]rD@YOUtD@VO]vD@AOU
